item.title: Dulce Et Decorum Est (Annotations)
item.description: Poem Stanza 1 Bent double, like old beggars under sacks, Knock-kneed, coughing like hags, we cursed through sludge, Till on the haunting flares we turned our backs,

item.title: Forces
item.description: What can forces do to an object? Forces can Change the shape, Change the size, Change the state of rest or motion, Bring about turning effect on objects, and exert pressure on objects Weight and Mass Forces Forces are a push or pull There are many different kind of forces Here is a free body diagram of a skydiver
